So Friday night after an uneventful night at the bar, i was cleaning up as usual and all i heard was a screech and a thud. naturally i went outside to see what happened and i could still see the smoke from the deployed airbags lingering in the air. So i wasn't the first one on the scene but i was one of the firsts. So the driver must have taken the turn at the intersection at about 30-50 MPH. She lost control of her car and hit the first 3 cars parked in the parking lot, across the street from the bar. after hitting the 3 cars she hit and took out the light post and stopped. The girl then got out of her car and RAN up the street away from the accident, leaving her friend in the car. Some drunk college kids pulled the kid out of the car and laid him on the sidewalk, while others were trying to get the horn to turn off. As the kid was laying on the ground bleeding the people who pulled him out of the car were fighting over who knew CPR, but he was still breathing making this not a necessary issue. I started pushing back the growing crowd, and telling them to get the hell out of the way because the paramedics were on the way. Naturally this didn't work as kids kept crowding around and taking pictures with their cells phones of this bleeding kid and the fucked up car. while i was pushing back the crowd i got a look at the kid and looked into his eyes.  Not only did he have not a clue wat was going on but i think he had an instant concussion. as far as i know this kid is doing ok, and the girl was still at large. that was on saturday.   

I cant explain how creepy it was to look into the eyes of someone who is literally GONE, and has no idea what's going on. I think it was almsot as if he thought he way dying, his eyes were scanning back and forth across the sveral faces looking at nothing in particular, but trying to make sense of it all, and for that one instant we locked eyes and connected. It was a haunting image for me to look upon and is one what is bured into my Mind and probably will be forever. Empty eyes searing back and fort seeing things we can only just begin to fathom. Wondering if everything is going to be ok or if in-fact this is it.

Well where to start other then it's WEEK 4, and you all know what that means. This weeks candidate managed to spray his Douchiness, not only all over me, but also to cote the restaurant where I was eating in the fine distinct oder of April Mist. Mr Douche bag of the week 4, was sitting at the booth across the wall divide from me. While eating my dinner I had the prestigious honor of hearing him Scream about how his friends Martini should not be garnished with a lime. "Hey buddy." he said to his latino waiter, " Tell your bartender that a martini should never come with a lime". Now call me crazy but a High end bar like Pedro's Mexican Restaurant, should know better, right? I mean this is after all, Pedro's Mexican Restaurant, where the most popular drink on the menu is a Margarita, Which is coincidentally garnished with a LIME, and well the most popular beer is Carona and well that comes with a lime too. After the lime fiasco, this douche then begins to talk with his latino waiter about his trip to mexico, and how he loved being in Cancun, which I'm sure our latino friend could give to shits about because its the Wisconsin Dells of Mexico. Now call me crazy but someone who's been to Mexico, and loved it should know the difference between an enchilada, and a burrito, thus bringing us to round 3 of douching.  After listening to this stimulating conversation about the finer points of mexican cuisine, Douche Bag decided he wants to eat a taco, THANK GOD THEY NEVER ASKED IF HE WANTED HARD OR SOFT SHELL. After deliberating about the price of a single taco versus the platter of 3, which is they way they are served, he orders the fucking 3lb burrito. Needless to say, the only thing this guy is good for is figuring out to the exact cent what 15% of your total bill is.        This post is for you MR. Douche, who proves that in life some people can squeeze a quarter into 75 cents, but most of us just don't give a FUCK.

Well where to start this is also an update for my human conflict class. Well after our discussion about passive aggressive people.  I tend to see myself as someone who is open and direct with my feelings regarding a situation but I find when I deal with people who are passive aggressive that I also resort to using passive aggressive tactics. I do have to say I do hate it when people play those games with me because its clear avoidance of stating what the problem/issue is. I like people to be open and direct with me not hint at what the problem might be, because they eventually resort to well what do you think it is, and when you guess wrong you are in even more shit then you were before.  I come from a family that is open and direct and we deal with problems and issues head on, we yell, fight, scream, and then cool off and eat dinner. I think being more direct about your problems instead of being passive aggressive about it leaves the people in the confrontation in a much better place. Everyone knows where they stand, and the lines are cut and clear, there is no gray area, and the discussion is done, there is no re-opening of the wound so to speak.
